snippet.textDisplay: "Equality is a right, it doesn't deserve credit"... There's a lot of shallow thought around equality, summed up by this statement (I'm not saying Dave is shallow, he's clearly highly intelligent). Equality is an outcome which has never existed in any society of any nation throughout history, and there's no reason why it should. But that's not because certain groups are being oppressed more than others, it's because groups are inherently different. Attitudes, cultures, attributes, genetics, morals, priorities... that's without even considering geographic, climatic, environmental differences between areas. "Equality" is a simple term for an immensely complex situation, and it's so easy to blame "inequality" on oppression, racism, discrimination when in reality there are many other significant factors at play. Your parenting will have far more of an effect on your success in life than almost anything else, and it's well known that blacks have a higher % of absent fathers than any other group.

snippet.textDisplay:
This song is only racist to those who think racism against black people doesn't exist.

I'm Arab and Muslim, I've had my fair share of stereotypes, disrespect, insults, shackles, etc. But nothing of that compares to being born a black person. I grew up in Iraq post war, our neighbours were black but I never saw color, they were our neighbours, our friends when they laughed we laughed, when they cried we cried in my mind there was nothing preconceived about them and then I moved to the UK and the older I grew I started seeing, hearing and reading about racism and to this day I can't get my mind around it, I don't understand it, the concept of judging someone by skin colour is foreign and I'll never allow myself to understand it because it should never be something we let be part of our existence. Keep it foreign, keep it rejected, never give it the chance or thought. Black is beautiful, brown is beautiful, white is beautiful humanity is beautiful, don't let those who are blind to ruin who we truly are.
